  <static seed="98" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionMultiplicationWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>A few years back, a car was purchased for <m>{\$18{,}000}</m>. Today it is worth <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of its original value. What is the car<rsq/>s current value?</p>
<p>The car<rsq/>s current value is <fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/>.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\$3{,}000</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>When we use the word <lq/>of<rq/> in situations like <lq/><m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of <m>{\$18{,}000}</m>,<rq/> we can translate <lq/>of<rq/> into the multiplication symbol.</p>
<p>In this problem, to find <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of <m>{\$18{,}000}</m>, we do:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{6}}} \cdot 18000 
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{6}}} \cdot \frac{18000}{1}  \\
      \amp = \frac{1}{1} \cdot \frac{3000}{1}  \\
      \amp = 3000
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The car is worth <m>{\$3{,}000}</m> now.</p>
</solution>
